{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"88db2659-6b2a-434b-848d-2ed4faa36a18","content":"Here's how to migrate from **VSTest@3** to **Microsoft.Testing.Platform** in Azure DevOps:\n\n### 1. Update your test projects\n\nAdd/update these NuGet packages:\n\n```xml\n<PackageReference Include=\"MSTest\" Version=\"3.8.0\" />\n<!-- Replaces MSTest.TestAdapter + MSTest.TestFramework -->\n```\n\nEnable the new platform in your `.csproj` (or `Directory.Build.props`):\n\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <EnableMSTestRunner>true</EnableMSTestRunner>\n  <TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\n### 2. Replace `VSTest@3` with `DotNetCoreCLI@2`\n\n```yaml\n# Before\n- task: VSTest@3\n  inputs:\n    testSelector: 'testAssemblies'\n    testAssemblyVer2: '**\\*.Tests.dll'\n    codeCoverageEnabled: true\n\n# After\n- task: DotNetCoreCLI@2\n  displayName: 'Run tests'\n  inputs:\n    command: test\n    projects: '**/*.Tests.csproj'\n    arguments: >-\n      --configuration Release\n      --logger \"trx;LogFileName=results.trx\"\n      --results-directory $(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults\n      --collect \"Code Coverage\"\n```\n\n### 3. Publish TRX results & coverage\n\n```yaml\n- task: PublishTestResults@2\n  displayName: 'Publish test results'\n  condition: always()\n  inputs:\n    testResultsFormat: VSTest\n    testResultsFiles: '$(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults/**/*.trx'\n\n- task: PublishCodeCoverageResults@2\n  displayName: 'Publish code coverage'\n  condition: always()\n  inputs:\n    summaryFileLocation: '$(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults/**/*.cobertura.xml'\n```\n\n> If you want Cobertura-format coverage (recommended for `PublishCodeCoverageResults@2`), add a `runsettings` file or pass `--collect \"XPlat Code Coverage\"` instead, which uses the Coverlet collector.\n\n### Key differences\n\n| Concern | VSTest@3 | Microsoft.Testing.Platform |\n|---|---|---|\n| Runner | `vstest.console.exe` | `dotnet test` / native test host |\n| TRX output | Built-in | `--logger trx` |\n| Coverage | `codeCoverageEnabled` | `--collect \"Code Coverage\"` or `\"XPlat Code Coverage\"` |\n| Test filter | `testFilterCriteria` | `--filter` argument |\n\n### Tips\n- Set `condition: always()` on publish tasks so results appear even on failure.\n- Multi-TFM projects produce one `.trx` per framework — the glob `**/*.trx` handles this.\n- Remove any `<IsTestProject>` overrides that may conflict with `EnableMSTestRunner`.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"a81a8421-c817-4c8a-a45e-75a2717efa0f","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The directory is empty. This is a general question about migrating from VSTest@3 to Microsoft.Testing.Platform in an Azure DevOps CI pipeline. Let me provide guidance based on my knowledge.","outputTokens":804,"requestId":"3415:18DC0C:6FB42AF:7C16677:69F3FB32"},"id":"97b0753c-7647-48e3-9ee3-0c0b6bbfb062","timestamp":"2026-05-01T01:00:50.068Z","parentId":"b7cd4345-a547-4189-aba4-924f64559d05"}
